snippet.title: Build a Complete E-commerce Store with Admin Panel | API & Frontend | MERN Stack Tutorial | Class 5
snippet.description:
In this video, we’ll walk you through the process of building a fully functional E-commerce Store with a dedicated Admin Panel, using a separate API and frontend architecture. You’ll learn:

🔹 MERN Stack (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js)
🔹 REST API for seamless communication between frontend & backend
🔹 Admin Dashboard to manage products, orders, and users
🔹 User Authentication (Login/Register)
🔹 Product Listings, Cart, Checkout

By the end of this tutorial, you'll have a scalable, maintainable, and secure e-commerce application ready for production!

GitHub Repo Link: https://github.com/masifcoder/techmobiles

Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more beginner-friendly coding tutorials.

snippet.title: SLEEP With GOD'S PROMISES | 100 Psalms, Prayers & Bible Verses for Abundance, Healing, & Strength
snippet.description:
Join us as we dive into 100 powerful Bible verses from the Book of Psalms and challenge ourselves to uncover God's promises for abundance, healing, and strength.

We're constantly bombarded with messages that tell us we're not enough, we don't have enough, and we'll never be enough. But the Bible reveals a different truth-one that speaks directly to the heart of our deepest fears and desires. The Psalms are filled with God's powerful promises, offering hope, restoration, and divine strength.

At times, we struggle with doubt and wonder if God is really listening. The Bible reassures us that He is always near, and the Psalms reveal His faithfulness in every season of life. Whether we're facing financial hardships, battling illness, or searching for meaning, God's promises in the Bible remain unshakable. The Psalms remind us that His love never fails, and His plans for us are greater than we can imagine.

The Book of Psalms is a source of divine comfort and wisdom. Psalm 23 declares that God is our Shepherd, leading us beside still waters and restoring our souls. Psalm 27 reminds us that He is our light and salvation, giving us courage in times of trouble. Psalm 84 assures us that God blesses those who trust in Him, strengthening them for the journey ahead. Throughout the Bible, and especially in the Psalms, we see how God redeems, protects, and uplifts His people.

One of the most powerful Psalms, Psalm 138, declares that God's love endures forever and that He is working all things together for our good. This unshakable promise gives us hope and strength, even in our darkest moments.

The Bible is filled with life-changing truths, and the Psalms serve as a testimony to God's unwavering love. Today, I want you to know that these promises are for you-promises of abundance, healing, and strength. They're not just ancient words; they are living, breathing truths that can transform your life. Let these Bible verses from the Psalms remind you that no matter what you face, God is always working for your good.

localized.title: SLEEP With GOD'S PROMISES | 100 Psalms, Prayers & Bible Verses for Abundance, Healing, & Strength
localized.description:
Join us as we dive into 100 powerful Bible verses from the Book of Psalms and challenge ourselves to uncover God's promises for abundance, healing, and strength.

We're constantly bombarded with messages that tell us we're not enough, we don't have enough, and we'll never be enough. But the Bible reveals a different truth-one that speaks directly to the heart of our deepest fears and desires. The Psalms are filled with God's powerful promises, offering hope, restoration, and divine strength.

At times, we struggle with doubt and wonder if God is really listening. The Bible reassures us that He is always near, and the Psalms reveal His faithfulness in every season of life. Whether we're facing financial hardships, battling illness, or searching for meaning, God's promises in the Bible remain unshakable. The Psalms remind us that His love never fails, and His plans for us are greater than we can imagine.

The Book of Psalms is a source of divine comfort and wisdom. Psalm 23 declares that God is our Shepherd, leading us beside still waters and restoring our souls. Psalm 27 reminds us that He is our light and salvation, giving us courage in times of trouble. Psalm 84 assures us that God blesses those who trust in Him, strengthening them for the journey ahead. Throughout the Bible, and especially in the Psalms, we see how God redeems, protects, and uplifts His people.

One of the most powerful Psalms, Psalm 138, declares that God's love endures forever and that He is working all things together for our good. This unshakable promise gives us hope and strength, even in our darkest moments.

The Bible is filled with life-changing truths, and the Psalms serve as a testimony to God's unwavering love. Today, I want you to know that these promises are for you-promises of abundance, healing, and strength. They're not just ancient words; they are living, breathing truths that can transform your life. Let these Bible verses from the Psalms remind you that no matter what you face, God is always working for your good.

snippet.description:
🚀 Project React  → https://cosden.solutions/project-react
📥 Import React (Newsletter) → https://cosden.solutions/newsletter?s=ytd

Join The Discord! → https://discord.cosdensolutions.io
Source Code → https://github.com/cosdensolutions/code/tree/master/videos/long/react-hook-form-tutorial
VSCode Theme | Font → Material Theme Darker | Menlo, Monaco "monospace"

In this video we will learn about React Hook Form and Zod. React Hook Form is a form library in React that makes it really easy to create complex forms that scale really well. We are going to learn how to create a form with React Hook Form, how to implement our own validation and submit our data, and finally how to use Zod for validation to make it easy for us to create strong forms. Get ready, you are going to learn a lot in this React Hook Form tutorial for React.
